### [Acts Chapter 28](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#001.md)

[Acts](../../../bib/kjv/act001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">act 28:0</span></span>

Overview

[Act 28:1](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#001.md), Paul, after his shipwreck,
is kindly entertained of the barbarians; [Act
28:5](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#005.md), The viper on his hand hurts him
not; [Act 28:8](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#008.md), He heals many diseases
in the island; [Act 28:11](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#011.md), They depart
towards Rome; [Act 28:17](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#017.md), He declares
to the Jews the cause of his coming; [Act
28:24](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#024.md), After his preaching some were
persuaded, and some believed not; [Act
28:30](../../../bib/kjv/act028.htm#030.md), Yet he preaches there two
years.

